# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Next.js project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` package using npm
- Package version added to dependencies

### 2. Code Changes
**Modified: `src/app/layout.tsx`**
- Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component at the end of the `<body>` tag in the root layout
- Placed after existing providers to ensure proper initialization order

## Implementation Details

The implementation follows Next.js App Router best practices:
- Used the framework-specific import path `@vercel/speed-insights/next`
- Added the component to the root layout to track all pages automatically
- Preserved existing code structure and component hierarchy
- Maintained TypeScript type safety (verified with tsc --noEmit)

## Next Steps

To complete the setup:
1. Enable Speed Insights in your Vercel dashboard for this project
2. Deploy the application to Vercel
3. Verify the tracking script appears in the page's head tag
4. Monitor performance metrics in the Vercel Speed Insights dashboard

